e.  Sure some guilds may choose to farm the Praesertiums, but with Earring of Solstice being mass produced with only slightly inferior stats (and arguably still better for casters), I don't really see this as a problem.  <br><br>Phantron <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFFF><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub28.ezboard.com/unightgod.showPublicProfile?language=EN>NightGod</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Holy #@!%...I dinged</span><br>  Posts: 763<br> <font color=#FF0000>(6/28/02 5:39:27 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub28.ezboard.com/fdrinal28133frm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=47.topic&index=1>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_mad.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Earring of Veracity</span><hr size=1> 1) Earring of the Solstice came out after these, as did Iron Cog...so the RVR was in line at the time the earring came into game, which technically was soon after Luclin came out (though there is some debate as to its actual time of implementation, but that's a whole nother thread), hence necessitating a comparison between this earring and Velious ones, not anything that came out since then, it's like saying the RVR on a Yak is way out of line because Centi Longswords are in the game now.<br><br>2) The real reward of this line of quests is the Arx key to get in and fight Seru-the earrings are just a nice sidebar. <p><table border=1><tr><td><center><b><font size=2><A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=20669">Higar Mettlebender</A></font></b><br> <font size=1><EM>Templar of the 56th Prayer, Luclin Loot Ho and 7th Shawl Owner</EM></center><table border=1 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 wi