re always there and I'm pretty sure they always drop the shard for Arx key.  If they made it you need Arx Key for Earring 3 you'll suddenly see way more Earring 3 being completed for sure<br><br>Phantron <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFFF><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub28.ezboard.com/unightgod.showPublicProfile?language=EN>NightGod</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Holy #@!%...I dinged</span><br>  Posts: 768<br> <font color=#FF0000>(6/29/02 6:12:08 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub28.ezboard.com/fdrinal28133frm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=47.topic&index=3>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_mad.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Earring of Veracity</span><hr size=1> You might be forgetting what earrings were around when this one was first discovered....it was one of the better earrings in the game at the time...people were drooling over it....there was absolute crap for earrings until SoL and especially CT came out. It just all seems so moot now that the solstice earings are in game-the RvR on them is insanely in the player's balance..I mean, you have to kill what? one blue to 60 mob and a couple greenies and have access to or the plat to afford the services of a handful of very skilled tradeskill players and a toon that can forage and boom....you have one of the best earrings in the game, good for pretty much every class (and if you're not sure you believe that, you should have seen the number of people, representing every class, from the top guilds on Drinal I sold steins and idols to, and I was one of three people or so actively selling to a large base of people).<br><br>Funny you should say that about the key being easier than earring 3...as I understand it, once you get your first Arx key, the mobs in the area it opens up drop reports like candy.<br><br>Just another time sink, but at least this one eliminates itself once it's finished once... <p><table border=1><tr><td><center><b><font size=2><A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=20669">Higar Mettlebender</A></font></b><br> <font size=1><EM>Templar of the 56th Prayer, Luclin Loot Ho and 7th Shawl Owner</EM></center><table border=1 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 width=100%><tr><td width=15%>Drinker</td><td width=10%>200</td><td width=15%>Potter</td><td width=10%>188</td><td width=15%>Jeweler</td><td width=10%>188</td><td width=15%>Fletcher</td><td width=10%>185</td></tr><tr><td>Smith</td><td>183</td><td>Brewer</td><td>180</td><td>Baker</td><td>175</td><td>Tailor</td><td>168</td></tr></table></td></font><td><center><b><font size=2><A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=129464">Jobago</A></font></b><br> <FONT SIZE=2><EM>Warrior of the 27th ded froggie<BR>Slayer of lots of little tings<BR>Erm...<BR>Dats about it</EM></font></center></td></tr><tr><td colspan=2><center><a href="http://pub82.ezboard.com/bguardiansofthekeep"><b><font size=2>Guardians of the Keep</font></b></a> - <a href="http://www.eqdrinal.com">Drinal</a><br>"These balls are making me testy!"</center></td></tr></table> </p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFFF><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub28.ezboard.com/uphantron.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Phantron</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>THogg's Master</span><br>  Posts: 15<br> <font color=#FF0000>(6/30/02 2:48:16 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub28.ezboard.com/fdrinal28133frm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=47.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_mad.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Earring of Veracity</span><hr size=1> I think the drop like candy remark is made because stuff in Arx Seru is a lot more abaundant since they probably respawns fast (to prevent you from fighting Seru without adds).  I believe Arx Seru is a relatively open area and it'd be hard for me to imagine pathing in Arx Seru can be worse than the Consillium buildings.  When I had good faction with Seru farming was pretty smooth, and I got a report in the first 3 or so hours.  However once you lose faction with Seru you have to worry more about many hazards such as freak pathing, super GMs, CR, etc.  How are you supposed to get into a Consillium when you're KOS to the GM stuck at the entrance who sees invis and hits like a NToV drake?  <br>  <br>Of course I agree that RvR is heavily balanced in player's side for PoTC.  But seeing PoTC is unlikely to be nerfed, is it too much to ask the quest made a least a little bit easier especially when the difficulty preventing the quest comes from bad game design?  Camping 3 hours per report, I can stand that, but when you can't even get inside the area to camp reports, that's just frustrating. <p><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=90049>Phantron</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFFF><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub28.ezboard.com/uchaidduskwalker.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Chaid Duskwalker</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>THogg's Lubba</span><br>  Posts: 9<br> <font color=#FF0000>(7/1/02 6:48:53 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub28.ezboard.com/fdrinal28133frm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=47.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_mad.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Earring of Veracity</span><hr size=1> &gt;&gt; How are you supposed to get into a Consillium when you're KOS to the GM stuck at the entrance who sees invis and hits like a NToV drake?  &lt;&lt;<br><br>The same thing you do in every similar encounter --  you get a monk to move it away.<br><br>The earrings of veracity aren't about RvR.  It's about timesink vs. reward.  That's the defining aspect of Luclin quests.  There are alternatives if you need a see invis item.  The only reason people would do the veracity quest at this point, with the shitty pathing and horrible report drop rate, is if their guild was gearing up for Lord Inquisitor Seru.  Considering none of the guilds on this server are even close to that stage, it's going to be a while before you see more than a handful of people with this quest earring. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub28.ezboard.com/fdrinal28133frm9.showPrevMessage?topicID=47.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub28.ezboard.com/fdrinal28133frm9.showNextMessage?topicID=47.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub28.ezboard.com/fdrinal28133frm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=47.topic&index=5><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/fr/themes/default/addReply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"><a href=http://pub28.ezboard.com/fdrinal28133frm9.threadControl?topicID=47.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/fr/themes/default/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub28.ezboard.com/fdrinal28133frm9.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=47.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub28.ezboard.com/fdrinal28133frm9.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=47.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><fo